President Obama has signed an Executive Order to create a Presidential Emergency Board to help resolve a dispute between the Southeastern Pennsylvania Transportation Authority and some of its employees. The board will hear evidence and deliver a report within 30 days, recommending how the dispute should be resolved. President Obama has appointed Richard R. Kasher as the chair of the board, along with Ann S. Kenis and Bonnie S. Weinstock as members. Kasher has extensive experience as an arbitrator and has been appointed by several presidents to serve on emergency boards. Kenis and Weinstock are also experienced arbitrators and have served on various arbitration panels.